Arrays:
	Array is a container which is used to store collection of elements with same data type
	Array used to store multiple values in a single variable.
	Store data based on index.
	Index will start from "0".
	When u create an empty array and do not assign value to the array, default value will be stored.
	Arrays are fixed in size — once created, you cannot change their length.
	Memory allocated in Heap to store the elements of the array.
	Memory allocated in stack to store the variables /references.
	
Array declaration:
	data_type[] variableName;
Array creation:
	variableName=new data_type[size];  //size should be positive integer
	
Array declaration + creation:	
	data_type[] variableName=new data_type[size];
	int[] arr=new int[3];
		
Initialize the array:
	arr[0]=1;
	arr[1]=2;
	arr[2]=3;
	arr[3]=4; -->array index out of bound exception
	
Types of Array:
	1. Single dimension
	2. Multi dimension